The Deity Goes to the Beach
We will be waiting at Mikage Shrine!
The skies are clear, and she has not a care on her mind.
She is going into town to buy a few things.
A toothbrush, sponges, and duct tape.
You know that abandoned shrine at the top of the hill?
The one that is supposed to have all those paranormal phenomena, right?
I heard that the ghost of a girl appeared not too long ago.
I told my children to not go near it.
I do not know what I would do if something were to happen to them.
The shrine is not a scary place!
I know it is not exactly extravagant,
but Tomoe still cleans the place every day!
They think it is haunted now.
That is why people do not come to the shrine.
I had not realized that people thought it was haunted.
Are not you supposed to be out shopping?
And what are you doing up there?
A bird got stuck in one of the branches,
and I felt like helping it out.
I need to do something about this.
We are going to throw a fall festival!
People will definitely come to the shrine,
and everyone will realize that it is not abandoned!
I do not want to have anything to do with events that attract visitors.
We held a special event like this once before.
Mikage-sama told us not to touch anything.
Is not that a portable shrine?
Nanami-sama, you must not touch that!
I wonder what it looks like!
First, I will scrub it clean!
Maybe that will make it look better.
What does she think she is doing with that old piece of junk?
And what do you think you are doing?
You could just help her if you are worried.
Honestly, I am surprised that you still refuse to see Nanami-chan as anything but a human.
All I see is a deity.
She is the only one who still sees herself as a mere human.
Thank you for your hard work.
A portable shrine is a place for a deity to live.
Someone with an actual body like you cannot live in it.
I do not think you have what it takes to throw a festival.
Why do not you just give it a rest?
For the time being, let us set aside the portable shrine.
Is there anything I can use in here?
It is not as if the disappearance of worshippers is a recent thing.
The shrine has always been like this, even before you took over.
Just because you are the Earth Deity now, it does not mean you have to let it bother you.
I want people to come and pray at the altar you work so hard to maintain.
The main building is free of dust.
The offering box does not have a single piece of trash in it.
I want everyone to see that.
And I know that I cannot do anything that a deity is capable of,
but I can at least do my best as a perso
You still have not realized it?
The air is so clean because you are here.
Abandoned shrines are magnets for miasma.
That is something even I cannot cleanse.
Remember how the place looked when you first arrived?
Do not you think it is become more beautiful since then?
Still, I do not want people to keep thinking that our shrine is abandoned and creepy.
We are throwing a festival soon, so please come by.
It is actually a quite charming and pleasant place.
A mortal deity is holding a special event, huh?
So, we have one week until the festival.
I am open to suggestions on what to do if you have any.
How about we get a whole bunch of sake,
And where do you think we will find that much?
You know, I do not like it when you put down others' ideas without suggesting your own!
We should catch demons and put them on display.
Both of their plans lack any common sense.
You need a permit from the Department of Health to hand out food at a festival.
You should call off the festival.
have you considered a more traditional festival?
One with a kagura dance and drawing fortunes.
Because I received a letter from Nanami.
She was apprehensive about letting you guys handle this on your own.
We put on a kagura dance once before in the past.
I did not tell you because I did not think you could handle it.
You can wear it over what you have on.
I am sure everything will turn out fine now that I have shrine guardian's seal of approval!
We are going to make sure you know this dance before the festival.
I will not go easy on you.
You are raising your hand too high.
How many times do I have to explain it to make you remember?
We have less than a week until your performance!
Do you think we have the luxury of taking it slow?
I am not going too fast.
How long are you going to keep sitting around?
Let us get back to practice.
I do not think anyone's going to stick around that long.
It is a deity job to cleanse the bad aura.
This is to commemorate the return of celebrations to our shrine...
so please do it completely and perfectly!
I think I would do better with some music.
He cannot even produce a sound yet!
Zip it, and get back to practice!
We do not have a second to waste!
My movements should not be that bad,
but I always freeze up in front of him.
Today, we are practicing until the fifth part.
Your hand is too high again.
Yes, now spin to the right.
Stop making me point out the same mistakes!
What do you think you are doing?
I know that you are nervous because you want the dance to be perfect,
but your nerves are precisely why you are messing up.
You should do this when you are feeling nervous.
It is an old tradition passed down in this shrine.
It is called swallowing a human.
It is a charm to remind you that you are a deity.
You will do a lot better now.
But I have done this many times when I was little.
Intelligence, I give her a C. Physical strength, D. Spiritual power and luck are also both C's.
Why on earth would Mikage-kun choose her?
I just do not get it.
I have put her through so many trials, like the Narukami-hime affair.
Well, she passed those tests nonetheless.
Yet I cannot shake off the feeling that she is unfit to be an Earth Deity.
Maybe Mikage-kun was mistaken after all.
I will have you know that I was not.
I picked her for a reason.
Now then, shall we get started with your final exam?
That is not how you do it!
I cannot even memorize the first part.
Tomoe said that he believed in me.
Not a surprise, coming from a girl who gets a paltry D for physical strength.
You are a rude little girl.
You should introduce yourself first, you know.
How do you know my name?
I am here to test Mikage's successor.
I will see whether you are fit or not to be an Earth Deity.
What was with herI mean, himher?
An Earth Deity should be able to cleanse thick miasma.
Now we will see whether you can, Nanami-chan.
The air was so clean yesterday!
Tomoe took such good care of this well too.
The air is so clean because you are here.
Abandoned shrines are magnets for miasma.
That is something even I cannot cleanse.
Remember how the place looked when you first arrived?
Do not you think it is become more beautiful since then?
What is the meaning of this?
The miasma around the shrine has become unbearably thick.
This is not normal, is it?
Is it because Nanami-chan's power cannot dispel it anymore?
I tried to clear it, but...
We will do something about it.
It is the Earth Deity's job to cleanse the land.
Do not move an inch from here!
Do not you have something stronger?
What do you think my precious sacred sake is?
It loses its power once it dries up.
I... did not live up to Tomoe's expectations.
I... could not do anything without his help.
I am going to town for a while, Tomoe.
Nanami cannot cleanse the miasma, and has thus fled the shrine.
Tomoe looks everywhere for her, but she is nowhere to be found.
Is this the last they will ever see of each other?
Next time, I Became a Deity!
